data.title: Weekend Wrap-Up: Globes Go Social, Breaking Dawn Sneak Sizzles, Owen Wilson Welcomes Baby
data.meta_description: Wonder how you did on the Golden Globes office pool? Miss the weekend's other entertainment news? No worries. We've got a cheat sheet for everything that has gone down in showbiz since you left work on Friday.
data.text:
Wonder how you did on the Golden Globes office pool? Miss the weekend's other entertainment news? No worries. We've got a cheat sheet for everything that has gone down in showbiz since you left work on Friday.

- Speaking of the Globes, The Social Network was the big dog, scoring four prizes including Best Motion Picture Drama. Here's our full recap as well scorecard of all the winners! We also have favorite quotes from the carpet, the juiciest backstage scoop and our picks for the best and worst moments of the show.

RELATED: The 10 best things ever said at the Golden Globes

- The weekend kicked off Friday night with The Social Network nabbing Best Picture at the 16th Annual Critics' Choice Awards. Check out the other big winners right here.

- The first pic from Breaking Dawn was released Sunday, revealing a steamy glance at Bella and Edward's honeymoon. Hubba-hubba!

- The Twitterverse drummed up yet another Justin Bieber death hoax --hours before was live and presentin' at the Globes.

- The Green Hornet buzzed this weekend's box office with $34 million, while The Dilemma bombed with just $17.4 million.

- We gave you five things to know about the final season of Big Love.

- After the passing of Touched By an Angel star John Dye at 47 last week, we took a look at five TV stars who died too young. We also remembered actress Susannah York, who passed away Friday from cancer at 72.

- Kanye West kicked off a Twitter spat with Britney Spears...then took it back.

- Another Desperate Housewives star is joining Eva Longoria on the Wisteria Lane divorcee block.

- Kim Kardashian and Kris Humphries may not be as serious as everyone thinks, pal Lala Vasquez told E! News.

- Despite reports that Brooke Mueller completed treatment and checked out of a sober-living house, E! News confirmed that wasn't the case.

- A guitar-smashing stunt sent The Game to the hospital to stitch up a deep gash in his finger.

- We delved into whether Camille Grammer could put the kibosh on Kelsey's February upcoming plans.

- Just five days after announcing he was going to be a dad, Owen Wilson and girlfriend Jade Duell welcomed a son Friday.
